{"TopicId":192151,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Cant fly straight to save my life","CreatedByName":"TylerRose22","CreatedById":203156,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-05T04:59:48Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"TylerRose22","CreatedById":203156,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-05T04:59:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowdy All,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just recently bought KSP and pretty frustrated right off the bat. I\u0027ve done most of the tutorials and really enjoyed those, but when I tried to start career mode on normal or easy, I cant do anything. I literally built the exact same \u0022flea\u0022 rocket from the basic rocket tutorial, and mine cant go up past 500m before it flips over and the parachute deploys. I\u0027ve added fins, turned on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E, tried to turn in all kinds of direction to prevent the flipping, but nothing works. Really bummed i spent money on a game I cant even play. Any help is appreciated.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is a link for a video of what happens\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/nkRtaiY\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://imgur.com/a/nkRtaiY\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OHara","CreatedById":162784,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-05T06:49:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou should put the cursor over the staging stack (lower right in assembly, lower left on the launchpad) select the \u0027\u002B\u0027 that appears to make a new position, and then drag the booster symbol below the parachute symbol.\u00A0 Then the staging stack will look\u00A0more like the lower right of the image (but just stages not three).\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage ipsAttachLink_image ipsAttachLink_right\u0022 data-ratio=\u002262.27\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 style=\u0022width:387px;height:241px;float:right;\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 alt=\u0022CU4ph4W.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/CU4ph4W.jpg\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nHitting the staging key (\u0027space\u0027 by default on PC) fires only the booster.\u00A0 You the staging key again later when you really want to open\u00A0the parachute.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is a famous trap for new players.\u00A0 There are more.\u003Cbr\u003E\nKSP was created in a way that requires new players to figuring out many things on their own ---\u00A0more figuring things out than most of us players would have preferred.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-05T09:11:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/203156-tylerrose22/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022203156\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/203156-tylerrose22/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TylerRose22\u003C/a\u003E. I just wanted to say: welcome to the Forums.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162784-ohara/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022162784\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162784-ohara/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@OHara\u003C/a\u003E already said everything about you problem that needs to be said: you activated the parachute at the same time as the engine, so it deployed and pullt your rocket over. And staging errors like that are something that happen to even the most experienced KSP players. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gogi","CreatedById":168144,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-05T11:12:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223752147\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192151\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583399498\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AHHans\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, AHHans said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/203156-tylerrose22/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022203156\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/203156-tylerrose22/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TylerRose22\u003C/a\u003E. I just wanted to say: welcome to the Forums.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162784-ohara/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022162784\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162784-ohara/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@OHara\u003C/a\u003E already said everything about you problem that needs to be said: you activated the parachute at the same time as the engine, so it deployed and pullt your rocket over. And staging errors like that are something that happen to even the most experienced KSP players. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHappens to me every time I start new career.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-05T12:42:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223752172\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192151\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583406728\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168144\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gogi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Gogi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHappens to me every time I start new career.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly when you start a new career?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEvery new craft of mine gets test-flown at least once to see if I got this kind of stuff right....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt least \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/203156-tylerrose22/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022203156\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/203156-tylerrose22/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TylerRose22\u003C/a\u003E got off the launchpad. It also took NASA at least one extra try to get that right: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7O4V7JfeTSU\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMercury-Redstone 1\u003C/a\u003E. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gogi","CreatedById":168144,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T09:48:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223752196\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192151\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583412157\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AHHans\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/5/2020 at 1:42 PM, AHHans said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly when you start a new career?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEvery new craft of mine gets test-flown at least once to see if I got this kind of stuff right....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt least \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/203156-tylerrose22/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022203156\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/203156-tylerrose22/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TylerRose22\u003C/a\u003E got off the launchpad. It also took NASA at least one extra try to get that right: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7O4V7JfeTSU\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMercury-Redstone 1\u003C/a\u003E. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo get engine and choute in the same stage\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}